<section class="common_page">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="col-md-12">
            <div class="main_container">
                <p>Flightsmojo.in, the B2C Online Travel Portal offers cheapest Domestic & International airtickets to all destinations on over 170 airlines worldwide. Most countries require VISA to enter their Country or some countries, depending on the Nationality, may allow Visa on arrival. Please refer to the respective country's official website to know the complete and accurate requirements.</p>

                <p>Check any transit visa requirements from the transit country's official website. Flightsmojo.in is not responsible or liable for any claims related to non-travel or difficulties to entry in any countries or even exit from originating country, due to lack of destination/transit visa/other mandatory travel/visa document(s).</p>

                <p>All countries have different Visa and documentation requirements. VISA are granted on merits at the description of each country, depending on the purpose of the visit.</p>



                <div class="payment_con">
                    <h3>Passport:</h3>
                    <p>To travel abroad, it is mandatory to have a valid passport to identify, the person, person’s details, and nationality and allow, to enter another country.</p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Passport must be valid for minimum 180 days from the date of outbound travel.</li>
                        <li>Passport must not be mutilated.</li>
                        <li>Must have sufficient pages for VISA & Immigration endorsement.</li>
                        <li>Hand written passports are no longer valid for travel.</li>

                    </ul>
                    <h3>Visa</h3>
                    <p>VISA endorsement (permission to enter) on passport, allows people access to that country, granting the visa for a specific duration stay and specify the reason for the visit. VISA’s for most countries must n=be obtain before traveling, unless Visa on arrival, is permitted.</p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Check VISA regulations of destination and transit countries.</li>
                        <li>Check validity of your VISA.</li>
                        <li>In case of Special travel permit, check with visiting country.</li>
                        <li>Ensure VISA and its validity for all Transit and destinations countries.</li>
                        <li>You may require Ticket, Invitation, and Travel & Medical Insurance.</li>
                        <li>Financial proof of support.</li>
                        <li>Some countries require certain vaccination to enter or exit, please check rules.</li>
                        <li>Embassy or their VFS service, may ask for any documentation, and have the right to reject any application without explanations.</li>

                    </ul>
                    <h3>VISA Categories:</h3>
                    <p>Different categories of Visa’s are available i.e.: Business, Tourist, Employment, Student, Medical, Entry Visa, and Immigration & Transit Visa. VISA rules may be obtained are available on the website of the embassies of different countries or from the countries, VISA facilitation service www.vfsglobal.com</p>
                    
                    <h3>Travel Documents to Nepal & Bhutan:</h3>
                    <p>Indian nationals do not require visa to enter Nepal & Bhutan. However Indian Nationals to travel require valid India Passport or original Indian Election Voter ID.</p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Identity Card issued by Embassy of India in Kathmandu & Bhutan.</li>
                        <li>Identity Card with Photo issued by Sub- Divisional Magistrate or any other officials above his rank.</li>
                        <p>Please check with your nearest travel agents for documents required by the Indian Immigration for Indians traveling to Nepal & Bhutan.</p>
                    </ul>
                    <h3>Travel Document to Sikkim & Arunachal Pradesh for Non-Indians:</h3>
                    <p>Special Travel Permit is required for Non-Indians travelling to Sikkim & Arunachal Pradesh, which can be obtained either from the Ministry of Foreign affairs or from the Department of Tourism of the state, please check details with the Tour Operator.</p>
                    <h3>Travel & Medical Insurance:</h3>
                    <p>The travel insurance is mandatory by most countries and is recommended to protect you from medical, baggage, flight delays losses. Obtain Travel & Medical insurance, for the duration of your travel, for your destination or transit country including for transit countries, to avoid any high cost of medical treatment in foreign country.</p>                         
                </div>

            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
